67
00:04:49,450 --> 00:04:50,830
- What?<br>- What?

68
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:56,800
<i>Well, asking the police to search for her...</i>

69
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,040
<i>Don't you think you are making too big of a deal?</i>

70
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:03,300
<i>He is right. If you overdo it, <br>Onee-chan might not feel comfortable coming back...</i>

71
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,680
<i>It's been four weeks already.</i>

72
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:07,620
<i>She hasn't been home for four weeks, which is a big deal.</i>

73
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:10,410
<i>Besides, don't you think it is strange that we can't contact her?</i>

74
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:13,200
<i>How can I stay calm?</i>

75
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,000
Yeah, I guess that is a problem.

76
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:20,620
Mom...

77
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:24,800
<i>[Online Novel NOVELING]<br>[Author: Moon Bunny Michaela] [Title: Chobiko In a Pocket]</i>

78
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:29,700
Wow, she is doing such a great job.

79
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,500
<i>What are you reading?</i>

80
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:35,660
This is an online novel that Horikiri-san has been writing.

81
00:05:35,660 --> 00:05:37,400
<i>Horikiri?</i>

82
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:44,100
-You mean Horikiri from 3-A class who has been missing?<br>-Shhh...

83
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,660
<i>Horikiri. Oh, on-line novel.</i>

84
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,750
<i>Moon?</i>

85
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:55,870
<i>- Who? Who do you think it is?</i><br><i>-This novel?</i>

86
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,600
Minami!

87
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:03,160
- Do you have a minute?<br>-Eh?

88
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:05,900
I have something to ask you.

89
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,400
<i>What? This is Horikiri?</i>

90
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:12,000
<i>I haven't heard the name for a long time. Let me see.</i>

91
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
"Chobiko in a Pocket"?

92
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,000
- What's this?<br>- Well,

93
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,700
I heard she is an on-line novel writer.

94
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,620
<i>Seriously?</i>

95
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:24,400
<i>Moon Bunny Michaela is her pen name.</i>

96
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,800
<i>- Wow!<br>- Moon Bunny Michaela?</i>

97
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,600
What's this about?

98
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,000
Is it true?

99
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,200
- Yeah.<br>- Wait. Isn't she supposed to be in Tokyo for the dance workshop?

100
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,200
<i>Yeah, right.</i>

101
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,000
Horikiri-shi is in trouble.

102
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,000
<i>Ri...Riku?</i>

103
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:45,600
How dare you play dumb until now.

104
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:49,000
There are tons of things I want to ask you,

105
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,120
- such as your Chobiko...<br>- Huh?

106
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,200
Chobiko?

107
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:58,100
I'm talking about the figurine in your pocket.

108
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:01,500
What?

109
00:07:02,450 --> 00:07:04,620
You are still playing dumb?

110
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,300
Gosh, you are so good at acting.

111
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:11,040
You might as well become an actor.

112
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:17,400
Riku, do you know about this?

113
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,800
What?

114
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,500
They say it is Chiyomi.

115
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,800
Moon Bunny Michaela. She writes online novels...

116
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:31,200
Horikiri-san is now very famous.

117
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,900
Moon Bunny Michaela, was it?

118
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,800
Did you know about it?

119
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,100
No...

120
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:39,700
Is that so?

121
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,600
<i>My goodness, now he knows!</i>

122
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:48,700
<i>I will be in trouble if he reads it. What should I do?</i>

123
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:52,790
<i>Wait. Minami-kun is not the type who reads something like that.</i>

124
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,500
<i>Well, I guess it'll be okay.</i>

125
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,450
<i>It sure is Chiyomi.</i>

126
00:08:01,450 --> 00:08:03,400
This is 'Chiyomi's World.'

127
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,200
Then, what you are saying is

128
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:10,100
that Chiyomi has been writing... online novels?

129
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,000
It definitely is Chiyomi.

130
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,400
I am relieved. Ever since I heard she hadn't attended the workshop,

131
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,600
I was really worried.

132
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,100
But, it is good that she is updating it frequently, at least.

133
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:22,400
But why did she have to leave the house?

134
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:26,000
That's right. She didn't have to do this secretly.

135
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:31,000
Well, I suppose she felt shy about showing it to you.

136
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,200
But, why did she hide it from us?

137
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,700
Right?

138
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,600
I'm sorry.

139
00:08:41,460 --> 00:08:43,520
Actually, I did know

140
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:47,290
- that Horikiri-shi was Moon Bunny Michaela.<br>- Eh?

141
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:51,100
I'm sorry, Amippe.

142
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:56,620
I didn't want to say something that Horikiri-shi had kept secret.

143
00:08:56,620 --> 00:09:01,300
Hey, that's not good. You should have told us about it first thing.

144
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:03,160
I'm sorry.

145
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:05,410
On the day I told her that I knew about it

146
00:09:05,410 --> 00:09:09,500
and how I love Moon Bunny Michaela and Horikiri-shi,

147
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,600
she disappeared.

148
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,600
So, I felt responsible.

149
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:16,000
Takagi-san, it is not your fault.

150
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,400
The reason why Onee-chan disappeared

151
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:22,700
has nothing to do with her writing activities as Moon Bunny Michaela.

152
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:30,200
... That's what I think.

153
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:37,400
You should have told us if you knew about it.

154
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:41,600
I am sorry. I thought it would be better if Onee-chan told you about it herself after she came back.

155
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:47,400
Oh... She has been thinking about these kinds of things.

156
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:53,000
And, she is... how should I say... expressing herself?

157
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:58,000
I didn't know she had this kind of talent.

158
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:01,200
Now that I think about it,

159
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:06,200
she told us she saw a tiny person and got really excited about it.

160
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,200
<i>You saw One-inch Princess?</i>

161
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,600
<i>Yes, One-inch Princess.</i>

162
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,600
<i>What are you saying? That's not possible.</i>

163
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,250
<i>But, she was really there.</i>

164
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:19,400
<i>- On the river. I was with Minami-kun --<br>- That's enough. I am busy.</i>

165
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:23,450
Maybe she really did see her.

166
00:10:23,450 --> 00:10:26,200
She does have the tendency to daydream.

167
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:30,500
You know, there is not a clear distinction between reality and a dream for children.

168
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:33,200
Maybe I shouldn't have scolded her that much.

169
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:38,000
I wonder if...

170
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,120
Onee-chan became a tiny person for real?

171
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:45,870
Hey, what are you saying?

172
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:52,700
But, she must have had a lot of things she wanted to say but couldn't.

173
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:03,890
Shunichi is late.

174
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:08,140
He said he'd go for a run but hasn't come back yet.

175
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:13,710
What is he doing, leaving Chiyomi-chan behind?

176
00:11:13,710 --> 00:11:15,210
What?

177
00:11:25,290 --> 00:11:30,840
<i>[The Big Guy prepared this red dress for me.]</i>

178
00:11:32,810 --> 00:11:36,450
<i>[He must have just casually chosen it.]</i>

179
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:43,260
<i>[Even so, he wouldn't have given me <br>something that didn't suit me.]</i>

180
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:49,080
